column5: it was a dyed kind of rice paper.  I got it at DeSerres.  They have other colors too and ones with leaves infused in them.  I'll attach a few below to show  you and you can show your boss.  So the first one is a squid on brown, leaf infused paper:     This one is of some small butterfish on cream leaf infused paper:      Tell him to experiment too.  You can get some really neat fish at the T n T Market.  This one was one of my favorites, but it sold.  I wish I had of kept it, but I can make another:
Great work as well Joey!!!,I would also like a black and orange if/when you get a chance to make them. The smaller 10's if there's a choice.Thanks Dave.
Okay, well when I get back from Nipissing, I'll make up a bunch of orange/black and post a thread for anyone interested.  Thanks Dave!!
Very nice work Joey.Takes a lot of talent, along with paitience, to do such things. Well done!
Wow, your photos and artwork is amazing!!! Well done.  BTW awesome looking in-lines too!
Awesome stuff Joey good luck up north this weekend.
Thanks everyone.  I really enjoy doing them.  Only a few more days.  Just ticking off my checklist and slowly packing stuff!!!

Been a busy girl here!!  We're heading to Lakair for musky opener and I thought I'd make a few new lures to entice the beasts.  I think I'm ready now.  The blades are 10's and 12's.   Also, I've been doing artwork called Gyotaku, which is a fish rubbing of a fish on rice paper using printer block ink.  Instead of selling these two, I decided to get them framed for myself.  I don't think I like them together on the wall like that, but I'll decide later where I'm going to put them.  Just put them up to get a feel for where I want them to go.
Those lures are outstanding Joey, but where's the black with orange ??  Have a great trip and just leave me one 50"er  Hopefully your still there when we arrive on the 22nd.
Well unfortunately they did not have any black and orange left Lew  Oh well, maybe they'll like a new color this year  Yup, looking forward to seeing you!!!
Do we see some purple in it .
I love your Gyotaku Joey ! If you sell these prints anywhere, let me know, would love to buy one (or two) for my cabin (and home).
Dang Joey! You're good at everything you do! Those are beautiful!
Photography, Gyotaku, lure making. All done very well. You never cease to amaze.
you think the body of artwork is impressive, wait til you see her crank those double 12's in for 4 hours straight no breaks
Was gonna say that Lew!!!  Joey... I'll test the red and whites, the goldy and whites, and the black and gold too.  Free of charge. lol.  Good work.

Yup, purple people eaters   Yes, I sell them, I can shoot you a pm with the ones I have available right now if you'd like!   A shucks, thanks hon!   Well thanks Dan, how did those baby pics turn out?  I downloaded Adobe Photoshop and am absolutely lost now   Good arm workout Rog, can't wait, less than a week now   Dang, I know, I know, I wanted black and orange  Okay, I'll test them first okay  Thanks!!
Joey Gyotaku... what a great name...!  Interesting art work..
Joey, the first one in the bottom row...is that musky hair?
Looks like krystal flash to me. Nice stuff Joey!
Yup. I think you're right Christopher.
Patsy and I can (well Patsy can) testify to the fact that Joey's lures do work. She caught her PB at 49" on one of these.  I hope someone will show me one of these 12's.
Awesome work Joey!  Both the baits and artwork are very nice.    Good luck at Lakair!!

Thanks Kev, see you soon!    Yes, he's right, I had it lying around so thought I'd incorporate it.  Good eye Chris!!    Well I'll show you and  maybe you can be a beta tester for me Rich    Thanks Will.  Can't wait!

Gorgeous, let me know if you ever make orange and black...that's what I've caught my only musky on  Beautiful work Joey, you have a lot of talent, thanks for sharing with us...  Now I'll be watching for all the reports of Musky caught with those beauties!!!  Also love your artwork on the walls ... Maureen
FYI, I started posting at 3:30am...dang slow computer and dial up   you can disregard my comment on the black and orange  Maureen

They are great looking baits,,,,BUT,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,   Please use the net J.  Have a great time.  Betty and I thought about going up this year,but pop and mudder need some help ,so our holiday will be spend working a bit,and fishing a bit. Look forward to the report.
Oh,, she can do it..

Thanks Mo, and they will have the black and orange, they are just out of stock.  I'll let you know if I make some.  I'll save one for you   Awww, what a good son you are.  There's some good fishing up that way too B.  Thanks and yes, will use the net
Just saw this now. You're a woman of many talents, very impressive!
An artist you are!!

Joey:  Great artwork! My boss has recently been trying the same thing and so far has done a carp, herring, pumpkinseed, yellow perch and rock bass. He has only used white paper so far and was very impressed with the one you did with the black background. Was that black rice paper or was it dyed?  Jon
